01:00:37.240 --> 01:00:39.830
So, if you actually have RLlib working

01:00:39.840 --> 01:00:42.270
and you're happy with it, then

01:00:42.280 --> 01:00:44.510
you can keep it. I would still suggest

01:00:44.520 --> 01:00:46.870
not using puffer's vectorization maybe,

01:00:46.880 --> 01:00:48.550
but at least throwing our emulation

01:00:48.560 --> 01:00:51.630
wrapper on the environment. Because then

01:00:51.640 --> 01:00:53.710
