01:01:58.680 --> 01:02:00.070
by default,

01:02:00.080 --> 01:02:01.990
like eight is a very common batch size

01:02:02.000 --> 01:02:04.150
for Atari, is that people are hyper

01:02:04.160 --> 01:02:06.630
focused in on sample efficiency for some

01:02:06.640 --> 01:02:08.110
reason in

01:02:08.120 --> 01:02:10.630
in RL, which yeah, makes sense if you're

01:02:10.640 --> 01:02:13.350
doing this for a robot, but RL is not

01:02:13.360 --> 01:02:15.310
just about robots, right? There are tons

01:02:15.320 --> 01:02:17.510
of tasks for which you have a simulator,

01:02:17.520 --> 01:02:19.510
the simulator is fast, the simulator has

01:02:19.520 --> 01:02:20.870
infinite data,

01:02:20.880 --> 01:02:22.150
you kind of just want to suck up as much

01:02:22.160 --> 01:02:24.270
